                "href": "/profile/Joseph-William-Gagin"
            },
            "answer_text": "Since I have been in the answer is no. do not pick up anything that is not yours. the chances of an item being attached to a bomb is too high to risk picking up a cool new toy. Even if that particular gun is not boobytrapped it might explode when you fire it due to CIA exploding ammunition left over from the Vietnam war. See project eldest son for more info. Stuff like broken enemy tanks and trucks are also dangerous. you don't know what they were transporting. maybe it is full of toxic residue from some homebrew bombs, maybe it got shot by an A10 and is full of depleted uranium dust that will give you cancer. ",
