                "name": "Steve Gerhardt",
                "href": "/profile/Steve-Gerhardt-4"
            },
            "answer_text": "Back in the Viet Nam days we could, subject to several restrictions. They had to be foreign made, no recaptured US stuff, and they couldn\u2019t be full auto. The SKS was very popular as were the Chinese and Russian bolt actions. I brought back a Chinese copy of a Russian Tokarev pistol. It had to be registered as a War Trophy, then I had to get a Viet Namese export permit and an American import permit. A lot of paperwork, but all that paperwork makes it more valuable. Fifty years later I still have it and shoot it. ",
