            "answer_text": "I don't think many, if any countries would let their soldiers bring back any weapons found on the battlefield. How ever, the actual Army or Regiments themselves, yes and all the time. Some for evaluation, and others for trophies. There are a few Argentine armoured cars outside officers messes in the UK after the Falklands war, and I think a Puccara was brought back as well. When I was down there in 85, we were still using an ex Argentine Unimog as a battered run about. ",
